article.description: Radford beats Cornell 74-61 in comeback win
article.headline: Radford beats Cornell 74-61 in comeback win
article.linkText: Radford beats Cornell 74-61 in comeback win
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Rashun Davis scored 19 points on 6-for-9 shooting to lead Radford to a 74-61 come-from-behind win over Cornell on Sunday. Trailing 38-32 at the break, Radford (8-4) opened the second half with a 14-0 run sparked by three straight buckets from Brandon Holcomb to build a lead it held on to down the stretch. Holcomb finished with 12 points and 12 rebounds, Javonte Green added 11 points and R.J. Price had 10 for the Highlanders, who shot 49.1 percent from the floor to extend their win streak to three. The Big Red held a 38-32 lead at halftime, but couldn't stop Radford after the break. Cornell was outscored 42-23 in the second half. Shonn Miller led Cornell (5-5) with a career-high 28 points and nine rebounds, while Robert Hatter added 18 points.
